# .dockerignore
# Files and folders to EXCLUDE from the Docker build context.
#
# When Docker builds an image it sends everything in the current folder
# to the Docker daemon. This file tells it what to skip.
# Without this, Docker would send node_modules/ (300MB+) every build!

# We install packages fresh inside the container via "npm ci".
# Sending pre-installed node_modules from your Mac would be slower
# AND might contain Mac-specific binaries that don't work on Linux.
node_modules

# Git history, GitHub Actions, and IDE settings have nothing to
# do with running the app — keep them out of the image.
.git
.gitignore
.github

# Test files are not needed in production. The image is for running
# the app, not testing it (testing happens in CI before build).
*.test.js

# macOS system files — junk in every Mac folder
.DS_Store

# Editor settings — not needed at runtime
.vscode
.idea

# Documentation
README.md
